Description: Fragment of double handle from a Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine red-brown; with some mica; cream slip. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Ermaios. Unpublished parallel in Athenian Agora. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 185, 19.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0128)
